            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong> over a medium-high heat</p><p>Once hot, add the<strong> torn jackfruit</strong> with the <strong>smoked paprika</strong>, <strong>ground cumin</strong>, <strong>cayenne pepper</strong> (can't handle the heat? Go easy!), <strong>agave nectar</strong>,<strong> soy sauce </strong>and pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and<strong> pepper</strong> and cook for 2-3 min</p><p>Add the <strong>tomato paste</strong> with 100ml <span class=\"text-danger\">[150ml]</span> <strong>boiled water </strong>and cook for 3-4 min further or until thickened to a pulled pork consistency</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
